The paper deals with auction theory and mechanism design, which are typically studied in the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Economics and Computation (cs.EC) sub-categories. The use of submodular valuation functions suggests a connection to Discrete Mathematics (cs.DS) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), where submodularity is a common concept. Finally, the study of equilibria and optimization in auctions is also relevant to Machine Learning (cs.LG).
